<taxonomicName authorityName="Costa &amp; Duarte &amp; Iannuzzi &amp; Grossi" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Dupuis" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[547,715,486,511]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Tetragus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="impunctatus">
<emphasis box="[547,715,486,511]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="219">P. impunctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the following characters: pronotal surface punctate (punctures large on concavity, fine on other surfaces) in male; surface of tergite VIII flattened to slightly convex in lateral view in female.
</paragraph>
